  "title": "Personal Assistant - Tuas Avenue",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Purpose</strong></h3><p>The Secretary provides comprehensive administrative and clerical support to ensure the smooth and efficient operation of the management office, supporting management staff with daily organisational, communication, and documentation tasks.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><strong>Administrative & Office Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage day-to-day office administration and clerical duties</p></li><li><p>Handle incoming calls, emails, and correspondence professionally</p></li><li><p>Schedule meetings, appointments, and maintain calendars</p></li><li><p>Prepare agendas, take minutes, and follow up on action items</p></li></ul><p><strong>Documentation & Records</strong></p><ul><li><p>Draft, type, format, and proofread letters, reports, and documents</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper filing systems (physical and electronic)</p></li><li><p>Handle confidential information with discretion</p></li><li><p>Manage records, contracts, and office documentation</p></li></ul><p><strong>Coordination & Communication</strong></p><ul><li><p>Liaise with internal departments and external parties</p></li><li><p>Coordinate travel arrangements and meeting logistics</p></li><li><p>Assist in organising company events, meetings, or workshops</p></li></ul><p><strong>Office Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain office supplies and liaise with vendors</p></li><li><p>Support basic HR or finance administrative tasks where required</p></li><li><p>Ensure office procedures and policies are followed</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></h3><p><strong>Education</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or equivalent qualification in Business Administration or related field</p></li></ul><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prior experience in a secretarial or administrative role preferred</p></li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></p><ul><li><p>Strong organisational and time-management skills</p></li><li><p>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook, PowerPoint)</p></li><li><p>High level of accuracy and attention to detail</p></li><li><p>Ability to multitask and work independently</p></li><li><p>Professional, discreet, and reliable</p></li></ul>",
